		<section class="wrapper style1 align-left">
			<div class="inner">
				<h2>QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS</h2>
				<p><span class="question">Why do we want to adopt?</span><br>
				Starting a family was a life-long dream of ours. We have so much to share with a child, that we can't wait to be dads. Throughout this process, we have always felt that adoption was our best option. We want to give a child the unconditional love, support and nurturing that has been given to us, so that he/she can live the best life possible.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Why would we make a good adoptive family?</span><br>
				We are a loving, caring, energetic, responsible, and fun couple. We get so much joy from being around our nieces, nephews and friends' children that we can’t wait to start a family and be dads. We enjoy our lives to the fullest but know that a child would bring us so much joy and happiness. Our friends and families are so excited to welcome a new addition to the family, and would shower us with love and support.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Where do we live?</span><br>
				We live in a diverse neighborhood called Edgewater on the north side of Chicago. We love our neighborhood and are very close to a lot of city parks, playgrounds, shops, restaurants and cafes.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Would we like to adopt a boy or a girl?</span><br>
				We would be delighted to adopt either a boy or a girl.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Do we have a set race or ethnic background in mind?</span><br>
				We do not have a race or ethnicity preference and are open to any racial or ethnic background. However, if we adopt a baby of another race or ethnicity, we would seek out resources, including support systems, friends and role models for the child to ensure that they had a supportive racial network. We value diversity and would always choose to live in a diverse neighborhood that was inclusive and open, so that had the child grew up with the best environment possible.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Are we looking only in Illinois (where we live)? Are you considering an international adoption?</span><br>
				No - we are looking to adopt from anywhere in the United States. We are not considering an international adoption. We would like to adopt domestically (from the US).</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">What age child will we consider for adoption?</span><br>
				Our goal is to adopt an infant 0-12 months old.</p>

				<p><span class="question">Would we consider siblings or multiples?</span><br>
				Yes, we would consider siblings or twins.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Are we working with an adoption agency?</span><br>
				Yes. We are working with an agency in Chicago, Illinois. Through the agency, we have completed a series of adoption classes, background checks and a home study. We are also certified in infant CPR and first aid.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Have we been approved by a state agency?</span><br>
				With the recent changes in laws in Illinois, we are approved by our adoption agency through a home study. However, it is no longer necessary for us to be a licensed foster care home through the state of Illinois.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">Are we planning a closed or open adoption?</span><br>
				We are open to however much or little communication and contact the birth parents would like to have. Our intention is that our child will always know his or her birth parents, and we will be happy to provide the birth parents with regular communication, photos, texts and in-person meetings.</p>
				
				<p><span class="question">I am considering placing my child for adoption and I would like to contact RJ and Jeff. What should I do next?</span><br>
				If you or someone close to you is considering placing your child for adoption, please contact us at <a href="mailto: rjandjeff@gmail.com">rjandjeff@gmail.com</a> or call <a href="tel:1-773-727-3152">773-727-3152</a>.</p>
			</div>
